CAPE TOWN - Cold and icy conditions are set to persist in the Western Cape. Mountains in Ceres and surrounding areas are covered in snow.Current weather conditions at the Matroosberg Nature Reserve. More #snow expected today! #eNCA @eNCAWeather @ajnarsee pic.twitter.com/TBWmRSKkwpThese weather conditions are expected to last until Friday.Emergency services are welcoming the freeze, as this can help combat the nearby Knysna fires.eNCA